I have a full workshop on people-pleading happening this Sunday. Buildyourboundaries.net to register!

Shoot me a DM if you have any questions!

node.text:
This clip is from a mini-episode of the Free Your Energy podcast. Grab it on Spotify or iTunes.

If you enjoy long-form podcasts, you'll love hearing me jam with world-class teachers, storytellers, and people with immense passion.

During the week, I do mini-episodes on different topics that inspire me!  If you NEED more words on overthinking, I have a mini-course called “How To Stop Overthinking.” You can grab that from Sylvestermcnutt.net/courses

I hope you get into the activity, action, and into the mud! It's the only way to create what you're envisioning!

Comment below and let me know what your thoughts are! 

Workshop Alert: On May 1st, I’m doing an immersive deep dive into the subject of letting go. This Saturday! 

I’ll teach you how to let go and how to enable the peace of mind you deserve. I’ll teach you how to recognize peace, and relinquish some of the threads that we hold on too yo tightly. 

Go to the link in my bio and reserve your spot in “The Art Of Letting Go Workshop.” I won’t teach this workshop again until the fall! See you Saturday!

node.title: The art of letting go of the “hero” mindset

node.text:
Good Morning 🌞! I’m sending you love from Arizona and I’m hoping this day supports your vitality and wellness! 

My thought of the day:

There is nothing more important than health and wellness. I'll invest my time and money into modalities and experiences that will improve my vitality.

I remember years ago, when I started to buy organic food, someone said to me, “Why would you spend your whole check on organic food when you could get cheaper stuff and have more money?”

Now look, I'm not here to shame that person or anyone who thinks that way. I also recognize that everyone has a different money situation, and I've been poor before, so I get it — you have to do what you have to do.

But I said to this person, “I don't give a damn about most of the things people are entertained with; what excites me is having excellent health, so I’ll spend my ‘whole check on my health’ and go get some more money because there's plenty of it. Plus, having better health means more money because money is nothing but energy.....”

I'm a firm believer in “If you want it bad enough, you'll find a way.” 

Investing in your health is always the way; it's always the mood, it's always worth it! Comment below and let me know how you feel today!

Also, there's a bunch of free things we can do to support our vitality:

• good sleep hygiene
• eating with your circadian rhythm
• daily mediation
• strength training
• calisthenics
• yoga and mobility training 
• walking 
• spending time in nature
• laughing
• reading

All free…

—————

I have two separate podcasts with @brandencollinsworth and with @fastingmd that covers this entire conversation. Stream the Free Your Energy podcast on all platforms.

node.text:
Drop a 💛 if this is for you!

I don't have time or energy to use on hating on others. It has never been my style. I mind my business and focus on the task at hand. It amazes me how certain people, programs, and organizations thrive off of negativity. Literally, certain people wake up, and before they can even clean up and brush their teeth, they already have negativity come out of their mouth, ha!

Respect yourself enough to build your boundaries with those people. Don’t let them drain you. Your energy is too precious and matters too much to waste on that vibration. I hope this week is good for you!

If you need a new podcast, consider adding the Free Your Energy podcast, where in each conversation all we’re doing is exploring different topics to help us all raise our vibration!

Sending love to all! #SylvesterMcNutt

node.text:
I had to share these via my book, Care Package: A Path To Deep Healing.

How to get: Amazon or discounted bundles via Sylvestermcnutt.net

Also available as an audiobook on amazon.

—————

I’ve made it to 114 days in a row without drinking alcohol. I cannot get on her and claim that I am “sober sober” from alcohol because I still don’t know yet.

I’m sober curious, a phrase coined by @rubywarrington, and yes, we have a 🔥 Free Your Energy podcast episode coming out in two weeks.

Why am I doing this? Simple, I believe In holistic health, and the truth is, vibrationally alcohol lowers your vibration. I’m experimenting to see how my vibration changes energetically, and after 114 days, the consequence of this experiment has been VAST.

I have a good test coming up. My birthday is August 23rd, and I’ll be with people I love in Florida, a place I love. I haven’t made my mind up on if I’ll have a drink or not, but I will keep you all updated here and on the podcast.

The last time I posted about my sober curious journey, the feedback was fire. I want to repeat; I’m not here to judge or shame anyone; this is out of love.

However, I am a disruptor of consciousness, and my job is to ask questions so that we can arrive at our highest energy.

Friend, with love, and if it feels appropriate to you — investigate your relationship with alcohol. Make sure you're choosing it, and you're not just going and blindly following society.

I hope you have a great week. Comment below and let me know what these words/atory bring up for you!

node.text:
Life update: my mental health is the best it’s ever been, and I’m so grateful to feel and to share this energy. One core reason is that I'm spending a lot of time doing what I'm passionate about.

I was thinking about “my passions” today. I realized that my two deepest passions right now are investing time and energy into serving my mind, body, and soul holistically (health) and asking questions (relationship building).

Maybe it’s the Virgo in me (Aug 23rd), but I love asking questions. Outside looking in, it would appear that writing and speaking are my passions, and they are too.

When I sit down to write a book, I sit down with one question in mind, and then I allow that question to turn into 56,000 other questions, and that’s how I like to write.

And when it comes to my health, I take it seriously, but I have fun. I’m a former football player, so I had to unlearn the bigger, faster, stronger mindset engraved in you from years of playing.

I had to open my heart to yoga and flexibility training as well so that my training is holistic.

I’m grateful to say that I have a few passions, and I’m fortunate because I get to experience the things I love with good people. I’m honored because I’m privileged too, and I don’t take anything for granted.

I hope you have the best week and if you connect with these words, drop a comment below. I would love to hear from you! #sylvestermcnutt

node.text:
“Cut them off” and “let them go” is what the internet will tell you, but that’s not realistic, practical, and is not how you build. It’s just another avoidance technique. I’m all about getting in the mud, creating a safe space for the hard conversations, and cooking the material that sits in our stories. 

Plus, I might not want to cut you off — I want you not to drain me. This is about respecting my boundaries.

So what do we do? Well, we use BOUNDARIES. That’s the safe answer. Boundaries create the container for us to respect each other’s energy, time, and space.

Boundaries are the way!

——
Workshop Alert: this Sunday, I’m teaching “How To Stop People Pleasing,” which is another energy drain.

Come on in, and I’m going to teach you step-by-step HOW to stop people-pleasing. Yes, the workshop will be sent out to everyone who registers in case you miss it live.

How to register: go to buildyourboundaries.net and register for the course. Yes, this workshop gives you access to my most popular course, Build Your Boundaries

Investment: $197 USD (one time)

People-pleasing is a consequence of a person routinely violating their boundaries. The number thing I’m going to teach you is self-forgiveness and self-compassion. Why? I don’t use shame to teach because shame doesn’t create transformation. Self-love does. I can’t wait to teach on Sunday!
